都市日報 - Authorities seek Xinjiang suspects in deadly Tiananmen Square crash probe 天安門爆炸　疑涉新疆人自殺式襲擊

Mainland police are searching for two suspects from the restive Xinjiang region after five people were killed and dozens injured when a car ploughed (猛撞入) into a crowd in Beijing’s Tiananmen Square yesterday.







 
Police in the capital are said to be asking hotels about suspicious guests (可疑賓客) who had checked in since October 1 and named two suspects it said were from Xinjiang.
Mainland police are searching for two suspects from the restive Xinjiang region after five people were killed and dozens injured when a car ploughed (猛撞入) into a crowd in Beijing’s Tiananmen Square yesterday.